London mr. Edmund Warnel
S. I have be fore mee yd of 29 past, & accordingly to yd order shall provide
the pancell of laces, which I hope will shew you that they be now really cheap
& good, I am sure I take as much paines as any ma can do to please his
freinds, for I am gouing, & desire to be commended in large my trade
as herefore be confident that I am in all respets
London m. Michiel Peeters
In antw aen den ul van 26 passato, tot als nogh toe en become van ul noeder
geen order ofte advijs, ende ten sij dat ick van alles woorde gedis chargeert, in
sal de lakens niet laten gaen, ofte m slaughter bett., want ick met geen aisie en
soecke te doen te hebben, maer wel een ijder het sijne te geeven, & gerust leeven
Ick dencke dat ul mij ten minsten soo verre betrouwt, dat ick u wel gedient hebbe
6 nu opt lest het & niet soude begeeren, over sulckx en tlast mij volgens hee
Ingesloten papier, 't welck ul breeder oock sal teekenen, & ick sal m. flanghter vol doen
E3 genee dan nogh sal comen, opleggen, waer naer ul sigh magh regueeeren
London n Gengelole
In answer op yy of 19 & 26 past, yd bill for acctt. of AN. is accepted pray
send mee notoniall a coppy of what m. de peyster did sig mee & Ill then roved
aganst hur, for he did itt without order I am fure, that so I might recoe
the £80- either from him or m. D. Viviaen, I have been of late much indisposed
and do still keep within doores, as soone I can go abroad shall endeavour to
end our concernes att least I do not beleave, that this yeare will be out, butt
@ 18 ditto
that all shall be payd & so remaine
London Will scawen
h
Sr. my last to you was on the 8: curitt to which referre you in answer to yd of
26h past, I hope the paquet I sent you be well arrived before this & that
you shall dispose of them for my acctt. as best you can though you beindy
an engagement to the contrary, for itt is onely for one or 2 parquetts &
stold mr. furnase of itt, besides bj them you may iudge what I am
sable to provide, if in the providing of some I could be servicable to
that portye, butt in case you pleases te keep itt to yd. silf, allow mee some
what for thes resico & onely the proision for what I keep still here, wich is vere well
assorted. beeng one curious parcell of about ƒ650- assorted to y advise. I do
as mich as I can to sell of our resting goods & hope to cleare itt this yea
towands y. comming over & so his yd handes

mons. ick ben grootelijk verwondert dat ul mij soo lanck seuldigh blijft ick hebbe

Turnhout Dew van Aagustijn Willems
jouff sedert dat ick op 9 august: twee lakens hebbe verkoght hadde de verbeloord

C 20 ditto 1681
weert Joan van Stalen
mons. op 21 August. hebbe aen ul gelevert ter weirde van ƒ 322:10: twe ckel
geloofde mij in 14 d te betaelen, het minste nu twee maende geleden is
suponeere ul tselve sal hebbe overt hooft gesien, daer entusschen mits ich
het goet soo goede coop aen ul hebbe gelaten dat het lanck dilayeeren souden
soadelijk wesen soo versoeke in antwoort deser de weirde aen mij gelieft te remedd
te meer alsoo present seer om gelt ben verlegen waer in ul in andere occasie
kan dinst doen gelieft becommandeeren
